# Project: empathic-credit-system

## Stack

- Python 3.11+ / `uv` (never use `pip` directly — use `uv add` / `uv run`)
- FastAPI + Uvicorn for the API layer
- scikit-learn, XGBoost for ML models
- SHAP for explainability
- Pydantic v2 for data validation
- Ruff for linting and formatting
- pytest for tests

## Conventions

- All API inputs/outputs must use Pydantic models.
- Every prediction response must include SHAP-based explanations.
- No `print()` in `src/` — use `python-json-logger`.
- Tests mirror `src/` structure under `tests/`.
- Run linter before finishing: `uv run ruff check && uv run ruff format`
- Run tests: `uv run pytest`

## Structure

```
src/api/           — FastAPI routes and schemas
src/data/          — Data loading and preprocessing
src/evaluation/    — Evaluation utilities
src/explainability/ — SHAP logic
src/models/        — Training and serialization
models/            — Serialized artifacts (not src/)
```
